The paper deals with algorithms for testing the existence of topological subgraphs in graphs, which is a problem in graph theory. The most relevant sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is the primary sub-category for graph algorithms. The paper also involves some computational geometry techniques, which makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) another likely sub-category. The problem of finding topological subgraphs is related to graph theory and combinatorics, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves some graph theoretic concepts such as immersions and subdivisions, which makes cs.GT (Graph Theory) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some complexity analysis, which makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
